The paper presents a novel technique for 3D face reconstruction using sparse photometric stereo and advances in face registration/modeling from a single image. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as semantic segmentation and geometric modeling (GR), as well as machine learning (MM) and computer graphics (CG) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of optimization techniques for calibration, which could fall under artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.CG, and cs.AI.
